<h2>In this tutorial:</h2>
<button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="trackAnchorClickSC('cpanel');">Change Email Password in cPanel</button>
<button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="trackAnchorClickSC('webmail');">Change Email Password in Webmail</button>
</div>

<center><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Vqvr9oI21cM" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></center>
<p>When you manage email accounts on your server, you may need to reset or change a password for one of your email accounts. You can reset or change your email passwords through your cPanel. The steps below will walk you through the steps to change an email account password.</p>
<p class="alert"><strong>Note!</strong> If you cannot access your cPanel, you can <a href="/support/website/cpanel/resetting-cpanel-password-amp">reset your cPanel password using AMP</a>.</p>


<a name="cpanel"></a>
<h2>Steps to change an email password in cPanel</h2>
<ol class="article_list">
<li><a href="/support/edu/cpanel/getting-started-cpanel/how-to-log-into-cpanel" target="_blank" title="Click here for info">Login into your cPanel</a>.</li>
<li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/cpanel/cpanel-email-accounts.jpg"><img style="float: right; margin: 0px 0px 15px 15px;"  title="Email Accounts in cPanel" alt="cpanel-email-accounts" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/cpanel/cpanel-email-accounts.jpg" width="100" /></a><strong>Select</strong> the &quot;<em>Email Accounts</em>&quot; from the &quot;<em>Mail</em>&quot; section.<br style="clear: both;" />
</li>
<li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/cpanel/cPanel-change-email-account-password.jpg"><img style="float: right; margin: 0px 0px 15px 15px;"  title="Change email password in cPanel" alt="cPanel-change-email-account-password" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/cpanel/cPanel-change-email-account-password.jpg" width="100" /></a>In the &quot;<em>Email Accounts</em>&quot; section, <strong>click</strong> on the &quot;<em>Change Password</em>&quot; link for the email account you want to change the password for.<br style="clear: both;" />
</li>
<li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/cpanel/change-email-password.png"><img style="float: right; margin: 0px 0px 15px 15px;"  alt="text" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/cpanel/change-email-password.png" title="Click here to view the larger image" width="100" /></a>Type a new password and <strong>click</strong> &quot;<em>Change password</em>&quot;. Note you must have a password strength of <em>at least</em> 50.
<br style="clear: both;" />
</li>
</ol>


<a name="webmail"></a>
<h2>Changing your email password in webmail</h2>
<ol class="article_list">
<li><a target="_blank" href="/support/edu/cpanel/cpanel-email/logging-into-webmail" title="Click for more information">Log into Webmail</a>.</li>
<li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/email/how-to-general/change-email-password/change-email-password-4-change-pass.gif"><img style="float: right; margin: 0px 0px 15px 15px;"  alt="Change email password Webmail" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/email/how-to-general/change-email-password/change-email-password-4-change-pass.gif" title="Click here to view the larger image" width="100" /></a>At the bottom of the webmail main page, click <strong>Change Password</strong>. <br style="clear: both;" /></li>
<li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/email/how-to-general/change-email-password/change-email-password-5-new-pass.gif"><img style="float: right; margin: 0px 0px 15px 15px;"  alt="Type New password Webmail" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/email/how-to-general/change-email-password/change-email-password-5-new-pass.gif" title="Click here to view the larger image" width="100" /></a>Change the password and click <strong>Change password</strong>. Note you must have a password strength of <em>at least</em> 50. <br style="clear: both;" /></li>
</ol>

<p>Read about all the features cPanel has. <a href="http://www.inmotionhosting.com/cpanel-hosting/cpanel-security-feature.html">Click here</a> to learn more. If you missed our previous article, please see the <a href="/support/edu/everything-email/introduction-email/writing-sending-email" title="Click here to view the previous article" target="_blank">Writing and Sending Email</a> tutorial. For more information on this course please visit <a target="_blank" href="/support/edu/everything-email/introduction-email" title="Click here to view the courses">Basic Introduction to Email</a></p> 
	
						 </div>

	






